definitions.definition: A vehicle that flies through space .
A finite pattern that reappears after a certain number of generations in the same orientation but in a different position .
The operator <=> in certain programming languages , which compares two values and indicates whether the first is lesser than, greater than, or equal to the second.

main_definition: ( astronautics ) A vehicle that flies through space .
secondary_definitions: ( cellular automata ) A finite pattern that reappears after a certain number of generations in the same orientation but in a different position .
( programming ) The operator <=> in certain programming languages , which compares two values and indicates whether the first is lesser than, greater than, or equal to the second.
